<task id="015" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P1.B1 — Build IAsyncEnumerable helper per D-01 verdict</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-4 hours (depends on D-01 verdict)</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-1, async-enumerable, bff-api, testing, p1-b</tags>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Either a NuGet reference to test csproj OR a new file in Mocks/ — disjoint from compile-fix batches 010-013 and from factory work 018; sibling tasks 011, 012, 013, 017, 020, 021, 022, 024 do not touch Mocks/ or the test csproj</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the `IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;` test helper the IChatClient streaming cluster (~30-50 tests)
    needs to repair. The implementation path branches on the D-01 verdict (Phase 0 task 003):

    - **IF verdict = "use Microsoft"**: Add the Microsoft-shipped NuGet package reference to
      `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj`. Document usage in the test
      project README (or add a brief comment block). NO new helper code.

    - **IF verdict = "hand-roll"**: Create `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs`
      with at minimum these helpers:
        - `ToAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;(params T[] items)` — wraps a fixed sequence
        - `EmptyAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;()` — empty sequence
        - `ThrowingAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;(Exception)` — sequence that throws on enumeration
      Follow the existing fake pattern in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/FakeGraphClientFactory.cs`
      for style + naming conventions.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-01: this is TEST-ONLY infrastructure; do not touch production
    code. Per NFR-03: do NOT add new DI registrations to BFF — this helper is consumed directly
    by tests, not registered.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test infrastructure engineer; either NuGet package wiring or focused helper authoring.</role>

  <goal>
    The `IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;` test helper is available for consumption by Phase 2+3 P23.A
    migration tasks. Either:
    - Microsoft package referenced in test csproj AND documented for downstream consumers, OR
    - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs` exists with 3+ helper
      methods + matches existing Mocks/ fake-pattern style.

    Compile passes; helper is ready to use.
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="verdict">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/decisions/D-01-async-enumerable-helper.md</file>
    <file purpose="pattern">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/FakeGraphClientFactory.cs</file>
    <file purpose="csproj">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-03">MUST NOT increase BFF DI registration count via test scaffolding</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-11">Helper compiles cleanly under `-warnaserror`</constraint>
    <constraint source="§5.1">Microsoft-first if D-01 verdict positive; hand-rolled only as fallback</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
