  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §3.4 the IChatClient streaming / `IAsyncEnumerable` mocking cluster is the
      largest single failure cluster (~30-50 tests). NSubstitute's auto-mock does not handle
      `IAsyncEnumerable` returns, producing the cluster's signature failure mode. The Phase 0
      researcher (task 003) decides Microsoft helper vs hand-rolled per §5.1 decision criteria;
      this task implements the chosen path. Phase 2+3 P23.A then migrates the affected tests
      using whichever helper this task ships.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="003" status="not-started">D-01 verdict file produced</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `decisions/D-01-async-enumerable-helper.md` for verdict + rationale. If file does NOT exist → HALT; report task 003 incomplete.</step>
    <step order="2">Branch on verdict:
      - IF "use Microsoft": go to step 3.
      - IF "hand-roll": go to step 5.
      - IF unclear: surface in `current-task.md` Decisions section, request owner clarification, halt.</step>
    <step order="3">[Microsoft path] Add the recommended NuGet `&lt;PackageReference&gt;` to `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj` at the version cited in D-01. Verify `dotnet restore` succeeds.</step>
    <step order="4">[Microsoft path] Add a short comment block in `Mocks/` README (or create one if absent) documenting which helper to call for `ToAsyncEnumerable` / Empty / Throwing scenarios. Skip to step 7.</step>
    <step order="5">[Hand-rolled path] Read `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/FakeGraphClientFactory.cs` to confirm style conventions (namespace, file-scoped namespace vs traditional, XML doc style).</step>
    <step order="6">[Hand-rolled path] Create `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs` with: `public static class AsyncEnumerableHelpers` containing `ToAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;(params T[] items)`, `EmptyAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;()`, `ThrowingAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;(Exception)`. Use `async IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;` syntax with `[EnumeratorCancellation]` where appropriate. XML doc each public method.</step>
    <step order="7">Run `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ -c Release -warnaserror`. Must succeed with 0 errors / 0 warnings on the helper.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` with chosen path, file/package added, and downstream consumer reference (P23.A migration in Phase 2+3).</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows changes ONLY under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/` and/or the test csproj — NOT under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">restore, build (-warnaserror)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code-or-package">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs (hand-rolled path) OR tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj (Microsoft path)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">D-01 verdict file consulted; chosen path documented in `current-task.md`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">EITHER Microsoft package reference added to test csproj AND documented, OR `Mocks/AsyncEnumerableHelpers.cs` exists with 3+ helper methods</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ -warnaserror` returns 0 errors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No modifications to `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`CustomWebAppFactory.cs` NOT modified</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new DI registrations added to BFF (NFR-03)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
